tur01.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ragefire Discussion/Question</span><hr size=1> I'm not to the point of Ragefire for my cleric epic.  But I will be soon.  Cleric Epics are probably one of the easier epics to obtain.  I also think it is by far the best epic as far as usefulness and not only greatly helps the user, but everyone on the server.  I have seen several clerics talk about difficulty getting to Ragefire due to others getting there first.  <br>
<br>
I know there are many clerics coming up that will need ragefire, and on a 1 week spawn timer this could become a bottle neck. <br>
<br>
Wonder a few questions:<br>
<br>
1) How many have had issues getting to Ragefire<br>
     It might turn out there is none<br>
<br>
2) If there are issues, would a reservation schedule for Ragefire be helpful?<br>
     Requirement for placing a Ragefire reservation would be completion of your epic up to this point, which Ragefire should be your last piece needed.  In other words, before making a reservation you MUST have Ixiblat and Chardok done (which I think you must if I remember correctly in order to make him spawn).<br>
<br>
Just wondering for discussion.... <p><img border="1" src="http://www.yellowspine.com/images/char1.bmp" width="360" height="94"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usadara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 500<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/23/01 5:48:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ragefire Discussion/Question</span><hr size=1> There are problems with getting to Ragefire, yes.  However, he is not a 1 week spawn.  In fact, he is a 0 to 72 hours pawn after Naggy dies.  Once he spawns for the first time, he is then a 23 hour spawn.  This particular spawn is the most frustrating part of the quest.  Only other part that is nutty is the Overking in Chardok.<br>
<br>
The best thing to do is keep yourself in the Sol B area and watch for him.  If he's up, you put together an impromtu raid and get what you need.<br>
<br>
I, personally, don't think Ragefire should be reserved.  He spawns frequently and as it is, the epic quest mobs aren't being reserved.  If we start reserving mobs like Ragefire, where will we stop?<br>
