<br>
Personally, I'm thankful to have passed the Chardok hurdle and certainly could not have done so without the help of so many friends.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, RL generally keeps me from raiding except on weekends so I can see the difficulty in gathering an impromptu raid for Ragefire.<br>
<br>
Although Ragefire will spawn several times in a normal Nagafen cycle getting to him is dependent on 1) Nagafen being killed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and 2) finding an available time for Ragefire in between the daily fire giant raids.  For me the only option seems to be signing up and running a random fire giant raid and hoping that Ragefire will be spawned at the time.  I would assume with so many clerics reaching this phase in the quest now fire giant raiders will be taking their guild clerics along to complete the epic so following another raid would be near impossible.<br>
<br>
